name: @ionic-native/android-fingerprint-auth
readme: Improve this doc # Android Fingerprint Auth ``` $ ionic cordova plugin add cordova-plugin-android-fingerprint-auth $ npm install --save @ionic-native/android-fingerprint-auth ``` ## [Usage Documentation](https://ionicframework.com/docs/native/android-fingerprint-auth/) Plugin Repo: [https://github.com/mjwheatley/cordova-plugin-android-fingerprint-auth](https://github.com/mjwheatley/cordova-plugin-android-fingerprint-auth) This plugin will open a native dialog fragment prompting the user to authenticate using their fingerprint. If the device has a secure lockscreen (pattern, PIN, or password), the user may opt to authenticate using that method as a backup. ## Supported platforms - Android
